Eight persons have been confirmed dead and several others were injured when a train rammed into a Lagos State government staff bus at the PWD bus stop in Ikeja, Lagos State. The South West Director of the National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA), Mr Ibrahim Farinloye in a statement issued on Thursday said eight adult female staff of the State Government died and d several were injured. According to him, the staff bus was trying to cross the PWD/Sogunle rail crossing while the train coming into Lagos from Abeokuta trapped the bus on its rail. Those who sustained injuries have been evacuated to the hospital, while operations are ongoing at the scene. Meanwhile, NEMA, Nigerian Police Force, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Civil Defence and Nigeria Railway Corporation team are presently on ground at the scene of the incident.   Muritala Ayinla Lagos commuters this morning watched with awe and consternation as a moving train crushed a passenger bus at the popular PWD Bus Stop along and dragged it to Oshodi Bus Stop. For over 30 minutes, motorists, passengers and other commuters who witnessed the accident were in shock… In "Metro & Crime" No fewer than 18 people reportedly lost their lives in a ghastly motor accident that occurred at the wee hours on Tuesday in Ekiti State. Eyewitnesses explained that apart from those numbers of people who lost their lives several also suffered serious injuries. However, the Ekiti Police Command in a… In "Metro & Crime" Olufemi Adediran, Abeokuta           Four persons were confirmed dead while nine others sustained varying degrees of injuries in an accident on Thursday morning along the Lagos-Abeokuta Expressway. The accident which involved a Mazda bus and an unregistered truck occurred at Obada Oko… In "Metro & Crime"